  "title": "Conversations, Act Four: A Healer's Bargain",
  "summary": "With Malign gone and the bar settling, the surgeon Brandis Finian sits down across from Lynae Caiton to decide whether she has changed enough to merit his aid. Wary and unconvinced, he presses her on whether she would resume torturing and killing if healed, and she explains the binding personal oath she has sworn to harm no one while sheltered among the Caspian people. Brandis senses through the Force that her punitive implant has already done grave damage and that fatal heart attacks are imminent. He agrees to help in exchange for a single future favor of his choosing, and Lynae swears the oath; taking her hand, he enters a healing trance and repairs her damaged heart enough to stabilize her. He instructs her to remain calm and arrange a hospital operating room so he can later remove the device entirely, and the two part on cautiously civil terms.",
